    tool_output=ToolOutput(
        output="Based on the provided S-1 document, there is an important distinction to clarify: **Net Income (Loss)** is reconciled to **Consolidated Adjusted EBITDA**, while the individual segments (Space, Connectivity, and AI) are reconciled from their respective **Income (Loss) from Operations** to **Segment Adjusted EBITDA**. \n\nBelow are the reconciliations and the specific adjustments made for both the segments and the consolidated company.\n\n### 1. Segment Reconciliations (Income from Operations to Segment Adjusted EBITDA)\nTo arrive at Segment Adjusted EBITDA, the company adds back specific non-cash and non-recurring operating expenses to the segment's Income (Loss) from Operations. \n**Adjustments made at the segment level include:**\n*   **Depreciation and amortization**\n*   **Share-based compensation**\n*   **Restructuring charges**\n*   **Impairment** (where applicable)\n\n**Three Months Ended March 31, 2026 (in millions)**\n| | Space | Connectivity | AI | Total Reportable Segments |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Income (loss) from operations** | **$(662)** | **$1,188** | **$(2,469)** | **$(1,943)** |\n| *Add:* | | | | |\n| Depreciation and amortization | 166 | 783 | 1,493 | 2,442 |\n| Share-based compensation | 145 | 116 | 378 | 639 |\n| Restructuring charges | — | — | (11) | (11) |\n| **Segment Adjusted EBITDA** | **$(351)** | **$2,087** | **$(609)** | **$1,127** |\n\n**Year Ended December 31, 2025 (in millions)**\n| | Space | Connectivity | AI | Total Reportable Segments |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Income (loss) from operations** | **$(657)** | **$4,423** | **$(6,355)** | **$(2,589)** |\n| *Add:* | | | | |\n| Depreciation and amortization | 757 | 2,376 | 3,568 | 6,701 |\n| Share-based compensation | 515 | 369 | 1,063 | 1,947 |\n| Restructuring charges | — | — | 487 | 487 |\n| Impairment | 38 | — | — | 38 |\n| **Segment Adjusted EBITDA** | **$653** | **$7,168** | **$(1,237)** | **$6,584** |\n\n*(Note: The text also provides identical reconciliation structures for Q1 2025, FY 2024, and FY 2023 using these same adjustment categories).*\n\n---\n\n### 2. Consolidated Reconciliation (Net Income to Adjusted EBITDA)\nTo reconcile consolidated **Net Income (Loss)** to **Consolidated Adjusted EBITDA**, the company applies the segment-level adjustments listed above, alongside adjustments for corporate, non-operating, and capital structure items.\n**Additional adjustments made at the consolidated level include:**\n*   **Interest expense**\n*   **Interest income**\n*   **Other (income) expense, net**\n*   **Provision for (benefit from) income taxes**\n\n**Consolidated Reconciliation Table (in millions)**\n| | Three Months Ended Mar 31, 2026 | Three Months Ended Mar 31, 2025 | Year Ended Dec 31, 2025 | Year Ended Dec 31, 2024 | Year Ended Dec 31, 2023 |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Net income (loss)** | **$(4,276)** | **$(528)** | **$(4,937)** | **$791** | **$(4,628)** |\n| *Add (deduct):* | | | | | |\n| Depreciation and amortization | 2,442 | 1,443 | 6,701 | 3,824 | 2,635 |\n| Share-based compensation | 639 | 232 | 1,947 | 784 | 679 |\n| Restructuring charges | (11) | 4 | 487 | 213 | 237 |\n| Impairments | — | 24 | 38 | 63 | 3,775 |\n| Interest expense | 664 | 447 | 1,945 | 1,580 | 1,693 |\n| Interest income | (213) | (117) | (492) | (371) | (249) |\n| Other (income) expense, net | 1,876 | 211 | 177 | (985) | 42 |\n| Provision for (benefit from) income taxes | 6 | 14 | 718 | (549) | (363) |\n| **Adjusted EBITDA** | **$1,127** | **$1,730** | **$6,584** | **$5,350** | **$3,821** |\n\n---\n\n### Summary of Why These Adjustments Are Made\n1. **Operating / Non-Cash Adjustments (Segment & Consolidated):** Depreciation, amortization, share-based compensation, restructuring, and impairments are added back to strip out non-cash accounting charges and one-time anomalies. This provides a clearer picture of the core, ongoing cash-generating ability of the Space, Connectivity, and AI operations.\n2. **Non-Operating / Capital Structure Adjustments (Consolidated Only):** Interest and taxes are added back/deducted to isolate the company's raw operational performance from its specific debt load (interest), tax jurisdictions, and non-operating financial events, allowing for better comparability against peers.",
